	<content>
        <h2>compile</h2>
        <p>
            With the <strong>compile</strong> command it's possible to compile the project including its
            dependencies.
        </p>

        <h3>Usage</h3>
        <p>
            <code>resolver [options] compile</code>
        </p>

        <h3>Arguments and Options</h3>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <td>-w [path]</td>
                <td>--working-dir [path]</td>
                <td>Makes it possible to specify the working directory to execute in.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>-s</td>
                <td>--silent</td>
                <td>Disables all log messages</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>-d</td>
                <td>--dependencies</td>
                <td>Only compiles the dependencies of the project.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>-p</td>
                <td>--project</td>
                <td>Only compiles the project and leaves the dependencies as is.</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <h3>Exit Code</h3>
        <p>
            This command will exit with the code 0 when it succeeds; 1 in case of an error.
        </p>
	</content>
</makedocs>